# Library Admin Panel - Coding Guidelines for AI Assistants

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js 16 Admin Panel using App Router with Server-Side Rendering (SSR). The project is ADMIN-ONLY (no public frontend).

### Architecture:
- **Admin Routes**: `app/(admin)/admin/[module]/page.tsx` - Admin pages
- **Admin Components**: `components/admin/*.tsx` - Admin-specific components
- **UI Components**: `components/ui/*.tsx` - Shadcn/UI components
- **API Client**: `lib/api/admin/` - Admin API integration
- **Auth**: Cookie-based authentication with `cms_sfb_token`

## Architecture & Rendering Rules

### Server Components First (CRITICAL)
- **Default**: All components are Server Components (NO "use client")
- **Only add "use client" when**:
  - Using React hooks: useState, useEffect, useCallback, useMemo
  - Using browser APIs: window, document, localStorage, sessionStorage
  - Using event handlers: onClick, onChange, onSubmit, onKeyDown
  - Using Next.js client hooks: usePathname, useRouter, useSearchParams
  - Using third-party client libraries: react-hook-form, sonner toasts

### Admin Pages Are Client Components:
- All pages in `app/(admin)/admin/` use "use client" for form handling and state management
- Components in `components/admin/` are mostly client components for interactivity

## File Structure & Naming

### Admin Routes
- Pattern: `app/(admin)/admin/[module]/page.tsx`
- Export: `export default function ModuleAdminPage()`
- Always include "use client" for interactive pages

### Admin Components
- Pattern: `components/admin/ComponentName.tsx` (PascalCase)
- Export: `export function ComponentName()` or `export default ComponentName`
- Most are Client Components due to form/state requirements

### UI Components (Shadcn/UI)
- Pattern: `components/ui/component-name.tsx` (kebab-case)
- Export: `export { Component, type ComponentProps }`
- Follow Shadcn/UI conventions

## Import Patterns

### Path Aliases (ALWAYS use @/ for cleaner imports)
```tsx
import { adminApiCall, AdminEndpoints } from "@/lib/api/admin";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import ImageUpload from "@/components/admin/ImageUpload";
import { getLocalizedText } from "@/lib/utils/i18n";
```

### Import Order
1. React/Next.js imports
2. Third-party libraries (lucide-react, sonner, etc.)
3. Local components (@/components)
4. Local utilities (@/lib)
5. Types/interfaces

## Admin API Integration

### Using Admin API Client
```tsx
import { adminApiCall, AdminEndpoints } from "@/lib/api/admin";
import { toast } from "sonner";

// GET request
const response = await adminApiCall<{ data: any[] }>(
  AdminEndpoints.news.list
);

// POST request
const response = await adminApiCall(
  AdminEndpoints.news.create,
  {
    method: 'POST',
    body: JSON.stringify(formData),
  }
);

// Error handling
try {
  await adminApiCall(endpoint, options);
  toast.success("Lưu thành công!");
} catch (error) {
  toast.error(error.message || "Có lỗi xảy ra");
}
```

## Internationalization (i18n)

### Admin manages multilingual content (vi/en/ja)

### LocaleInput Component
```tsx
import { LocaleInput } from "@/components/admin/LocaleInput";

<LocaleInput
  label="Tiêu đề"
  value={data.title} // Can be string or {vi, en, ja} object
  onChange={(value) => handleChange('title', value)}
  locale={locale}
  type="text"
/>
```

### Locale Utilities
```tsx
import { 
  getLocalizedText, 
  applyLocale,
  getLocaleValue,
  setLocaleValue 
} from "@/lib/utils/i18n";
import { getLocaleValue as getAdminLocaleValue } from "@/lib/utils/locale-admin";

// Get text in specific locale
const text = getLocalizedText(data.title, 'vi');

// Apply locale to entire object
const localizedData = applyLocale(data, 'vi');

// Admin-specific locale handling
const value = getAdminLocaleValue(data, 'title', 'vi');
```

## Form Handling

### React Hook Form Pattern
```tsx
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";

const { register, handleSubmit, formState: { errors } } = useForm();

const onSubmit = async (data) => {
  try {
    await adminApiCall(endpoint, {
      method: 'POST',
      body: JSON.stringify(data),
    });
    toast.success("Saved!");
  } catch (error) {
    toast.error(error.message);
  }
};

<form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
  <Input {...register("title", { required: true })} />
  {errors.title && <span>Required</span>}
  <Button type="submit">Save</Button>
</form>
```

## Media Library Integration

### ImageUpload Component
```tsx
import ImageUpload from "@/components/admin/ImageUpload";

<ImageUpload
  value={imageUrl}
  onChange={(url) => setFormData({ ...formData, image: url })}
  label="Hình ảnh"
  required
/>
```

### MediaUpload Component (Multiple Files)
```tsx
import { MediaUpload } from "@/components/admin/MediaUpload";

<MediaUpload
  value={images}
  onChange={(files) => setImages(files)}
  multiple={true}
  maxFiles={5}
  label="Gallery"
/>
```

## Translation Controls

### AI-Powered Translation
```tsx
import { useTranslationControls } from "@/lib/hooks/useTranslationControls";
import { AIProviderSelector } from "@/components/admin/AIProviderSelector";

const {
  handleTranslate,
  isTranslating,
  selectedProvider,
  setSelectedProvider
} = useTranslationControls();

// Translate field from vi to en
await handleTranslate('vi', 'en', data.title.vi, (translated) => {
  setData({
    ...data,
    title: { ...data.title, en: translated }
  });
});

// UI
<AIProviderSelector
  value={selectedProvider}
  onChange={setSelectedProvider}
/>
```

## UI Components (Shadcn/UI)

### Common Components
- `Button` - Primary actions
- `Input`, `Textarea` - Form inputs
- `Select` - Dropdown select
- `Switch` - Toggle boolean
- `Card` - Content container
- `Table` - Data tables
- `Dialog` - Modal dialogs
- `Tabs` - Tab navigation
- `toast` (sonner) - Notifications

### Usage Example
```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
import { Label } from "@/components/ui/label";
import { Switch } from "@/components/ui/switch";
import { toast } from "sonner";

<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Settings</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <div className="space-y-4">
      <div>
        <Label htmlFor="name">Name</Label>
        <Input id="name" />
      </div>
      <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
        <Switch id="active" />
        <Label htmlFor="active">Active</Label>
      </div>
      <Button onClick={() => toast.success("Saved!")}>
        Save
      </Button>
    </div>
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

## Authentication Patterns

### Protected Pages
All admin pages should be under `/admin/*` routes which are automatically protected.

### Token Management
```tsx
import { getAuthToken, setAuthToken, removeAuthToken } from "@/lib/auth/token";

// Check if authenticated
const token = getAuthToken();
if (!token) {
  router.push('/admin/login');
}

// Save token after login
setAuthToken(response.token);

// Logout
removeAuthToken();
router.push('/admin/login');
```

## Design System

### Color Palette
- **Primary**: `#006FB3` (Blue)
- **Secondary**: `#0088D9` (Light Blue)
- **Success**: `green-600`
- **Warning**: `yellow-600`
- **Error**: `red-600`
- **Muted**: `gray-500`

### Spacing
- Section padding: `py-8` to `py-12`
- Container: `container mx-auto px-6`
- Gap: `gap-4` or `gap-6` for spacing between elements

### Border Radius
- Small: `rounded-lg`
- Medium: `rounded-xl`
- Large: `rounded-2xl`

## TypeScript Guidelines

### Type Definitions
```tsx
type Locale = 'vi' | 'en' | 'ja';

interface NewsItem {
  id: number;
  title: string | Record<Locale, string>;
  content: string | Record<Locale, string>;
  slug: string;
  published: boolean;
  publishedAt?: string;
}

interface ApiResponse<T> {
  success: boolean;
  data?: T;
  message?: string;
}
```

### API Response Typing
```tsx
const response = await adminApiCall<ApiResponse<NewsItem[]>>(
  AdminEndpoints.news.list
);

if (response.success && response.data) {
  setNews(response.data);
}
```

## Code Quality Rules

1. **Always use TypeScript types** - No `any` unless absolutely necessary
2. **Error handling** - Always wrap API calls in try/catch
3. **Loading states** - Show loading spinners for async operations
4. **Validation** - Validate forms before submission
5. **Accessibility** - Use semantic HTML and ARIA labels
6. **Responsive** - All UI should work on mobile, tablet, desktop
7. **Comments** - Document complex business logic in Vietnamese

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

### ❌ Don't:
- Use public API endpoints (they don't exist anymore)
- Use locale routing (no more /vi, /en, /ja routes)
- Import from deleted folders (pages/, components/public/, components/homepage/)
- Use ImageWithFallback from figma folder (may be deleted)
- Hardcode API URLs (use environment variables)

### ✅ Do:
- Use admin API endpoints only
- Use @/ path aliases for imports
- Use Shadcn/UI components from components/ui/
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Handle errors gracefully with toast notifications
- Show loading states during API calls

## Testing Checklist

Before considering a feature complete:
- [ ] Tested CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
- [ ] Tested form validation
- [ ] Tested error handling
- [ ] Tested loading states
- [ ] Tested on different screen sizes
- [ ] Verified no console errors
- [ ] Verified proper TypeScript typing
- [ ] Verified proper i18n for multilingual fields

---

**Remember**: This is an ADMIN PANEL only. No public routes, no locale routing, no public SEO needed.
